cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of internal representations learned by the network, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the NMT context vectors, which can be considered as an application of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of similarity measures, which can be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
